        "description": "Monte Carlo propagation of inlet flow rate uncertainty (±0.15 L/min, uniform) and rotational speed uncertainty (±15 RPM, uniform) onto predicted velocity magnitude field. 95th-percentile prediction interval reported."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-pressure-head",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-head curve validation — 3000 RPM",
      "description": "CFD-predicted pressure head compared against bench-top measurements across 4–8 L/min at 3000 RPM. Mean absolute error 4.2 mmHg; maximum deviation 7.1 mmHg at 4 L/min. Uncertainty quantification performed via Latin Hypercube Sampling over fluid viscosity and outlet pressure boundary.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/lhs-pressure-head",
        "type": "UncertaintyQuantification",
        "method": "Latin Hypercube Sampling",
        "sampleCount": 200,
        "description": "LHS over blood viscosity (±10%, normal) and outlet static pressure (±2 mmHg, uniform). Prediction intervals computed at 90th percentile."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) prediction vs in-vitro measurement",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis compared against in-vitro loop measurements at 5 operating points. Predicted NIH values fall within 18% of measured values at 4 of 5 points; the 5 L/min 2000 RPM point shows 31% over-prediction attributed to recirculation zone sensitivity. This ValidationResult does not include an uncertainty quantification record; the modelling team considered the scatter in in-vitro replicates sufficient characterisation but did not formalise a UQ analysis object.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH within 25% of in-vitro mean across all 5 operating points.",
      "comparisonMetric": "Percent deviation from in-vitro mean NIH"
    }
